response_parts.content:
{
  "response": [
    {
      "id": 0,
      "translated": "Love Live! Superstar!! Yuigaoka Broadcasting Station, Liella!"
    },
    {
      "id": 1,
      "translated": "This is the Yuigaoka Girls' High School Suggestion Box, where we introduce your messages."
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "translated": "Alright everyone, let's say it together! One, two... Suggestion Box!"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "translated": "Okay, let's read some mail."
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "translated": "First, we have one from Liella name: Miku."
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "translated": "Thank you! They say, \"I attended both days of the 7th Live in Kanagawa and watched the Aichi show via stream. Mei-chan's solo song, 'Sky Linker,' started by taking the baton from the club president, Chisato-chan.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "translated": "Thank you so much."
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "translated": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "translated": "\"What was especially striking was the part at the end of the chorus where you thrust your fist forward. Since it happened several times, I was so moved I almost cried the first time, and from the second time on, I was thrusting my fist along with you.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "translated": "I totally get that."
    },
    {
      "id": 10,
      "translated": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "translated": "\"It was a performance where I felt the full extent of Mei-chan's straightforward strength, including her big heart, the kindness that embraces weakness, and her desire to protect.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "translated": "That's what they wrote."
    },
    {
      "id": 13,
      "translated": "Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "translated": "Thank you!"
    },
    {
      "id": 15,
      "translated": "Next is from Liella name: Baron Ojipan."
    },
    {
      "id": 16,
      "translated": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "id": 17,
      "translated": "Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "id": 18,
      "translated": "\"Regarding the impressions of 'Sky Linker,' the clapping with your hands near your face...\""
    },
    {
      "id": 19,
      "translated": "\"...and the side steps that followed looked like Flamenco, a traditional Spanish dance. Spain is often called the land of passion, and I felt you expressed Mei-chan's hidden passion through the dance. The moment I saw it, I thought, 'Whoa, that's so cool!'\""
    },
    {
      "id": 20,
      "translated": "Mm-hmm."
    },
    {
      "id": 21,
      "translated": "That's how they felt."
    },
    {
      "id": 22,
      "translated": "\"Well then, Ciao.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 23,
      "translated": "\"That's a Spanish parting greeting.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 24,
      "translated": "(Laughs) That's what it says."
    },
    {
      "id": 25,
      "translated": "Thank you! Ciao!"
    },
    {
      "id": 26,
      "translated": "Thank you so much."
    },
    {
      "id": 27,
      "translated": "Ciao!"
    },
    {
      "id": 28,
      "translated": "Alright, next is Liella name: Red-haired Kana. Thank you!"
    },
    {
      "id": 29,
      "translated": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "id": 30,
      "translated": "\"Seeing 'Sky Linker' on Day 1 in Kanagawa was truly the best. Yabu-chan's dance was so cool I can't get it out of my head. The song and lyrics are great, so I listen to it constantly. I'd love to see the dance for 'Sky Linker' again somewhere!\""
    },
    {
      "id": 31,
      "translated": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "id": 32,
      "translated": "That's what they sent in."
    },
    {
      "id": 33,
      "translated": "Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "id": 34,
      "translated": "Thank you!"
    },
    {
      "id": 35,
      "translated": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "id": 36,
      "translated": "I want to hear more about this."
    },
    {
      "id": 37,
      "translated": "'Sky Linker' was so cool. At first, I thought the performance might be done with a stand mic, just standing there and hyping up the crowd."
    },
    {
      "id": 38,
      "translated": "Right."
    },
    {
      "id": 39,
      "translated": "True."
    },
    {
      "id": 40,
      "translated": "I couldn't really imagine you doing an intense dance to it."
    },
    {
      "id": 41,
      "translated": "Yeah, yeah, yeah."
    },
    {
      "id": 42,
      "translated": "I kept wondering how it would turn out, but I never expected Flamenco in the instrumental break. It was a really valuable experience, though. You don't usually get to do Flamenco."
    },
    {
      "id": 43,
      "translated": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "id": 44,
      "translated": "That's true."
    },
    {
      "id": 45,
      "translated": "When I first saw the video of Mei-chan's choreography..."
    },
    {
      "id": 46,
      "translated": "I was like, \"What is this dance?!\""
    },
    {
      "id": 47,
      "translated": "Mei-chan was doing a style of dance that none of us had ever done before."
    },
    {
      "id": 48,
      "translated": "I said, \"Oh, this is amazing!\" and when I heard it was Flamenco, I was so surprised."
    },
    {
      "id": 49,
      "translated": "Yeah, I was like, \"How do you even do this?\""
    },
    {
      "id": 50,
      "translated": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "id": 51,
      "translated": "I couldn't do it at all at first."
    },
    {
      "id": 52,
      "translated": "No way, really?"
    },
    {
      "id": 53,
      "translated": "It used a core strength I'd never used before, and the whole foundation of the movement..."
    },
    {
      "id": 54,
      "translated": "How do I put it? The basics were totally different. I'm not an expert on dance or anything,"
    },
